<p>hereÂ´s my problem:  for a schoolproject i need to build a html5 page which is capable of starting different videos with a click on a button.  I use URI fragments to start and end a video at a certain point. The first video should loop until I start another video. If that other video ends the first video should start again. How can i do this ?</p>  <pre><code>    &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;  &lt;html&gt;    &lt;head&gt;  &lt;/head&gt; &lt;body&gt;  &lt;video id="example_video_1" autoplay="autoplay" loop="loop"  onended="run()" loop controls="none" width="640" height="300"&gt;     &lt;source src="video.mp4" type='video/mp4' /&gt;       &lt;p class="vjs-no-js"&gt;To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that supports HTML5 video&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;/video&gt;   &lt;script&gt;  videoPlayer = document.getElementById("example_video_1");   function run(){          var nextVideo = "Video1.mp4#t=11,19";         videoPlayer.src = nextVideo;         videoPlayer.play=autoplay;         videoPlayer.controls=controls;        };   function run2(){          var nextVideo = "video2.mp4#t=15,28" ;         videoPlayer.src = nextVideo;         videoPlayer.play=autoplay;         videoPlayer.controls=controls;    };  function run3(){          var nextVideo = "Video3.mp4#t=10,18";         videoPlayer.src = nextVideo;         videoPlayer.play=autoplay;         videoPlayer.controls=controls;       };   &lt;/script&gt; &lt;button onclick="run()"&gt;run1&lt;/button&gt; &lt;button onclick="run2()"&gt;run2&lt;/button&gt; &lt;button onclick="run3()"&gt;run3&lt;/button&gt;  &lt;/body&gt;  &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>